---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';

const bookTitle = 'Modern Compass';
const newsletterUrl = 'https://newsletter.themoderncompass.io';
---

<Layout>
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title="Modern Compass Book - Practical Framework for Personal Growth | Josh Imholte"
    description="Practical frameworks to navigate life with clarity and conviction. A personal growth book covering Self, Trust, Character, and Relationships with actionable activities and tools."
    canonical="https://themoderncompass.io/book"
    keywords="modern compass book, personal growth book, life direction framework, practical self improvement, character development, relationship building, Josh Imholte"
  />
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Book",
    "name": "Modern Compass",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Josh Imholte"
    },
    "description": "Map who you are before deciding who you become.",
    "url": "https://themoderncompass.io/book"
  }
  </script>
  <section class="book">
    <h1>{bookTitle}</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Map who you are before you decide who you'll become.</p>

    <div class="content">
<!-- Left column -->
<div class="details">
  <img
    src="/book-graphic.png"
    alt="Modern Compass book cover"
    class="book-graphic"
    width="780"
    height="780"
    loading="eager"
    decoding="async"
    sizes="(min-width: 768px) 320px, 70vw"
  />

  <h2>About the Book</h2>
  <p>
    The promise this book makes is to give you clarity about who you are before you decide what you do with that next. Once you have that clarity, a structured framework with defined directions and layers gives you the language and activities to map yourself honestly.
  </p>
  <p>
    Each layer comes with insights, activities, Minimum Requirements, and the Drag that keeps you stuck. The framework is structured, but since we're all unique and live different lives, seeing yourself mapped to it reflects a different picture based on your individuality. Once you've mapped who you are and understand what foundational or Drag work is needed, you can freely decide who you'll become next.
  </p>

  <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li>You feel stuck in loops of intention without action.</li>
    <li>You want clarity in relationships, career, or personal growth and do not know where to start.</li>
    <li>You have read personal growth books and ended up back in the same patterns.</li>
    <li>You want more than motivation. You want a compass you can carry with you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What You Will Gain</h2>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li>Confidence that grows from real world action instead of waiting for validation.</li>
    <li>Character that shows up as aligned choices you can point to.</li>
    <li>Trust that is informed and calibrated so you know when to extend it and when to hold back.</li>
    <li>Relationships that deepen past surface connection or confidence to release those that are no longer healthy to maintain.</li>
    <li>Momentum that replaces cycles of hope and inaction that starts with you.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Most people drift. They wait for a breakthrough or a sign. Nothing shifts until you take ownership of your direction. Modern Compass helps you build a personal system that keeps you moving forward even when life gets messy or foggy. It helps you stop second guessing and start navigating with conviction.
  </p>
</div>

      <!-- Right column -->
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <section class="excerpt">
          <h2>Excerpts</h2>

          <blockquote class="quote">
            Profound trust is the rare moment when you know without needing to ask that someone would
            protect the most vulnerable parts of you even if it cost them something.
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="quote">
            Confidence does not come from ignoring what people think. It grows when you apply yourself in
            the real world and build evidence of your own ability.
          </blockquote>
        </section>

       <section class="card orange">
          <h3>Publishing Approach</h3>
          <p>
            I plan to self publish so the book can stay practical and unfiltered. The goal is a clear
            and useful read with frameworks you can put to work the same day you open it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card blue">
          <h3>Follow the Journey to Launch</h3>
          <p>
            Modern Compass launches in January 2027. Subscribe to the newsletter to follow along as the book comes together—behind-the-scenes updates, early excerpts, and first notification when pre-orders open.
          </p>
          <a class="text-link" href={newsletterUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Subscribe to the newsletter →</a>
        </section>

       <section class="card purple">
          <h3>How to Engage</h3>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Subscribe to the newsletter.</li>
            <li>Reply to share your take on excerpts and tools.</li>
            <li>Try the worksheets and tell me what improved or what felt unclear.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .book {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .book h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .content {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  .details,
  .sidebar {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .details h2,
  .excerpt h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .details p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .bullets {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1rem;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .bullets li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }

  .cta-box {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
    background-color: #f6f7f8;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .cta-box h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: white;
    transition: transform 0.06s ease, opacity 0.1s ease;
  }
  .cta-btn:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .cta-btn.ghost {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--primary-color) inset;
  }
  .cta-btn.ghost:hover { opacity: 0.9; }

  .sidebar {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .excerpt { display: grid; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .quote {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #555;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
    background-color: #f2f3f5;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .card {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: #f9f9f9;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.04) inset;
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }
  .card p { margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }

  .text-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .text-link:hover { color: var(--accent-color); }

  .checklist {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0 1rem;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .checklist li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }

  .activity-lead { margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; }
  .activity-steps {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .activity-steps li { margin: 0.25rem 0; }
  .activity-close { margin: 0.5rem 0 0 0; }

/* Muted accent variations pulled from your gradient */
.card.orange {
  background-color: #fff4e6; /* pale orange */
}
.card.blue {
  background-color: #e6f0ff; /* pale blue */
}
.card.purple {
  background-color: #f8f0ff; /* pale purple */
}

.details, .sidebar { flex: 1; min-width: 0; } /* prevents flex overflow */

.book-graphic {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 320px;
  height: auto;
  margin: 0 auto 1.25rem auto;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .book-graphic {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0; /* aligns with heading on desktop */
  }
}
</style>
